FAQs
Is it expensive to study medicine in Hungary?

Tuition fees in Hungary vary depending on the university and program. On average, international students can expect to pay between €6,000 and €18,000 per year for medical programs. Additionally, living costs, including accommodation, food, and transportation, can range from €5,000 to €10,000 per year.
Do I need to speak Hungarian to study medicine in Hungary?

While Hungarian is the official language, many universities offer medical programs taught in English for international students. Proficiency in Hungarian is not typically required for admission to these programs, though learning some basic Hungarian can enhance your experience and help you navigate daily life more easily.
Are there scholarship opportunities for international students in Hungary?

Yes, there are various scholarship opportunities for international students in Hungary. Both the government and individual universities offer scholarships based on academic merit, financial need, and other criteria. These scholarships can significantly reduce the cost of tuition and living expenses, making it more affordable to study medicine in Hungary.
Can I work while study in Hungary?

Yes, international students in Hungary are generally allowed to work part-time during the academic year and full-time during holidays. However, it's important to check the specific conditions of your student visa and the regulations of your university. Part-time work can help cover some living expenses, but it's advisable to ensure you have sufficient financial support before arriving.
